=head1 DESCRIPTION

Provides information about a table cell in a table excerpt.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Header => Bool

C<TRUE> means that the table cell should be treated as a header.


=head2 Highlighted => Bool

C<TRUE> means that the table cell has a high enough confidence and is
relevant to the query, so the value or content should be highlighted.


=head2 TopAnswer => Bool

C<TRUE> if the response of the table cell is the top answer. This is
the cell value or content with the highest confidence score or is the
most relevant to the query.


=head2 Value => Str

The actual value or content within a table cell. A table cell could
contain a date value of a year, or a string value of text, for example.



